    <h1> Trees in Computer Science </h1>
    
    <section>
    <h2> General Information </h2>
    <p> Trees are a type of <span id = "emphasis"> data structure </span> used in many areas of computer science. </p>
    <p> One special type of tree is a <a href = "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Binary_tree#Types_of_binary_trees/"> binary tree</a>. An example of a binary tree is shown below.</p>
    <img src = "bintree.png" >
    </section>
    
    <section>
    <h2> Definitions </h2>
    <dl>
    <dt> Root node </dt>
    <dd> Topmost node in tree, has no parent node </dd>
    <dt> Parent node </dt>
    <dd> Node directly connected to a node beneath it </dd>
    <dt> Child node </dt>
    <dd> Node with a parent node. </dd>
    </dl>
    </section>
    
